00:18:25.300 --> 00:18:30.120
&gt;&gt; Ed Piskor: For a really long
time, I wanted to do some kind

00:18:30.120 --> 00:18:33.630
of comic using a lot
of hip hop imagery.

00:18:33.630 --> 00:18:39.500
A lot of my favorite kinds of hip
hop imagery, the fashion, graffiti,

00:18:39.500 --> 00:18:48.680 position:56%
pre-Ed Koch New York, like scary
New York, like Taxi Driver New York.

00:18:48.680 --> 00:18:50.560
And I didn't know what
the kind of McGuffin

00:18:50.560 --> 00:18:55.350
of whatever this tale would be,
and then at a certain point,

00:18:55.350 --> 00:19:01.880
I was just thinking when it comes
to all the cartoonists that I know,

00:19:01.880 --> 00:19:06.520
many are fans of rap music,
but they could never beat me

00:19:06.520 --> 00:19:07.820
in a trivia contest.

00:19:07.820 --> 00:19:09.120
You know what I'm saying?

00:19:09.120 --> 00:19:11.040
Just the inherent knowledge
of the records

00:19:11.040 --> 00:19:17.010
